items.question: Differentiate f(x) = x^2 - sec(x).
items.response:
f(x) = x^2 - sec(x)

f'(x) = d/dx (x^2) - d/dx (sec(x))

f'(x) = 2x - sec(x)tan(x)

The derivative is 2x - sec(x)tan(x).

items.question: Differentiate f(x) = x^2 - sec(x).
items.response:
f(x) = x^2 - \sec(x) \\
f'(x) = \frac{d}{dx}(x^2) - \frac{d}{dx}(\sec(x)) \\
f'(x) = 2x - \sec(x)\tan(x) \\
\text{Final Answer: } f'(x) = 2x - \sec(x)\tan(x)
